response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Find the First Duplicate\", \"description\": \"Write a function `find_first_duplicate` that finds the first duplicate value in an array of integers.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_first_duplicate(arr: list[int)) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list[int]): A list of unique integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- The first integer that appears at least twice in the input list. If no duplicate is found, return -1.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\ndef find_first_duplicate(arr: list[int)) -> int:\\n    seen = set()\\n    for num in arr:\\n        if num in seen:\\n            return num\\n        seen.add(num)\\n    return -1\\n\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == -1\", \"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 3]) == 3\", \"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 2, 1]) == 1\"] }"
